{
  "id": "fr_a1_lesson_015",
  "language": "fr",
  "level": "A1",
  "title": "Les loisirs",
  "description": "Talk about hobbies and free time with aimer/vouloir/pouvoir + infinitive — a guaranteed TEF/TCF speaking topic.",
  "metadata": { "estimatedMinutes": 9, "xpReward": 55 },
  "cards": [
    {
      "id": "c1",
      "type": "TextCard",
      "title": "Les loisirs",
      "content": {
        "subtitle": "Module 6 · Leçon 3",
        "body": "\"What do you like to do in your free time?\" is one of the most reliable TEF/TCF oral questions. Let's build the vocabulary and the three key verbs you need to answer well."
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c2",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "Aimer, vouloir, pouvoir + infinitif",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "These three verbs are almost always followed directly by an infinitive — no extra preposition needed, unlike some of their English equivalents.",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "j'aime / tu aimes / il aime", "translation": "I like / you like / he likes" },
          { "text": "je veux / tu veux / il veut", "translation": "I want / you want / he wants" },
          { "text": "je peux / tu peux / il peut", "translation": "I can / you can / he can" },
          { "text": "J'aime lire.", "translation": "I like to read." },
          { "text": "Je veux voyager.", "translation": "I want to travel." },
          { "text": "Je peux venir samedi.", "translation": "I can come on Saturday." }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 45 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c3",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "Le vocabulaire des loisirs",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "Common hobby vocabulary — note that \"jouer\" takes \"à\" for games/sports but \"de\" for musical instruments.",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "la lecture / lire", "translation": "reading / to read" },
          { "text": "la musique / le cinéma", "translation": "music / cinema" },
          { "text": "jouer au foot", "translation": "to play soccer (jouer à + sport)" },
          { "text": "jouer de la guitare", "translation": "to play guitar (jouer de + instrument)" },
          { "text": "faire du sport", "translation": "to do/play sports" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 45 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c4",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "le temps libre",
        "nativeTranslation": "le temps libre",
        "englishTranslation": "free time",
        "pronunciation": "luh tahn LEE-bruh",
        "ipa": "lə tɑ̃ libʁ",
        "partOfSpeech": "noun",
        "difficulty": "easy",
        "exampleSentence": "Pendant mon temps libre, j'aime lire et faire du sport.",
        "nativeExample": "In my free time, I like to read and play sports.",
        "audio": { "key": "fr/a1/temps-libre.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c5",
      "type": "InfoCard",
      "title": "Une question d'examen classique",
      "content": {
        "tone": "tip",
        "body": "\"Qu'est-ce que vous aimez faire pendant votre temps libre ?\" is a near-guaranteed TEF/TCF speaking question. Prepare 3–4 sentences about your hobbies using aimer/vouloir/pouvoir in advance."
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c6",
      "type": "FlashCard",
      "title": "Quick flip",
      "content": { "front": "faire du sport", "back": "to play/do sports", "hint": "Tap to reveal the meaning" },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 15 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c7",
